[unused] With international consensus having been reached regarding a treaty to combat climate change , a ``red light '' has been issued to South Korea 's heavily carbon - dependent industries .
[unused] Last Saturday , representatives of 165 countries finally agreed on the rules to implement the 1997 Kyoto Protocol after two weeks of negotiations held in Marrakech , Morocco .
[unused] According to the accord , about 40 industrialized countries must cut or limit emissions of carbon dioxide and other heat - trapping gases by an average of 5.2 percent from 1990 levels by 2012 .
[unused] Scientists believe these ``greenhouse '' gases ( GHG ) , which mainly result from burning fossil fuels , raise the earth 's temperature and change the climate by creating floods , droughts , and other abnormal weather phenomena .
[unused] As South Korea is not included in the Annex I parties , composed of industrialized countries , the accord , which is expected to go into effect some time next year , is not likely to affect the country for a while .
[unused] Although a member of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development ( OECD ) , South Korea is still regarded as a developing country and is not obliged to reduce its GHG emissions under the treaty .
[unused] But considering that South Korea has the highest growth rate of carbon dioxide emissions in the world , it will not be able to fend off international pressure to join in the global campaign to reduce greenhouse gases much longer , experts note .
[unused] According to statistics released by International Energy Agency ( IEA ) , a Paris- based agency affiliated with the OECD , South Korea was found to have recorded the highest growth rate of carbon dioxide emissions in 1999 , showing a 75.5 percent increase since 1990 .
[unused] In terms of the amount of emissions , South Korea discharged 410 million tons of carbon dioxide in 1999 , ranking tenth in the world .
[unused] If industrialized countries start cutting back on GHG emissions from 2008 , when the first target period begins , South Korea will become the seventh most carbon dioxide - producing country in the world , according to IEA figures .
[unused] But the government has not taken any concrete steps regarding the cutback of greenhouse gas emissions , maintaining a wait - and - see approach instead .
[unused] `` As South Korea has ` developing country ' status , we are not in a position to voluntarily express our course of action , '' said Yoon Jong-soo , director of the global environment office at the Environment Ministry .
[unused] `` We estimate Korea will probably join the countries cutting back emissions no later than 2018 .
[unused] Until then , we plan to step up efforts to gradually change our energy structure and reduce greenhouse gases by promoting research on renewable energy and energy - efficient technologies , '' he said .
[unused] Jun Mu , deputy director of the industry and environment team at the Korea Chamber of Commerce and Industry ( KCCI ) , said , ` `So far , industries have been rather passive in dealing with emission reductions , as is has been something that was considered to lie far off in the future .
[unused] ` ` We will first start gathering the opinions of business leaders regarding Korea 's ratification of the treaty , while continuing to promote the development of energy - efficient technologies , '' he said , adding a special committee on climate change was formed under KCCI last January .
[unused] The international treaty to tackle climate change was first envisioned in Kyoto four years ago , but due to the conflicting interests of developed and developing countries as well as other contentious issues such as emission reduction mechanisms and targets , it is yet to go into effect .
[unused] The protocol faced danger of being shelved altogether , when the U.S , which is responsible for one - fourth of all CO2 emissions in the world , decided to abruptly withdraw from the climate change treaty last March .
[unused] The Bush administration fears the treaty will have a negative effect on its economy and maintains that developing countries , such as China and India , should also be subject to mandatory emission targets .
[unused] But due to the strong initiative of the global community , led by the European Union , countries agreed on a set of rules to implement the climate change treaty _ with or without the U.S .
[unused] In order for the protocol to be implemented , it must be ratified by at least 55 parties , including enough industrialized countries to represent at least 55 percent of the total carbon dioxide emissions in 1990 .
[unused] A total 43 countries have ratified he treaty so far , with Korea yet to ratify .
[unused] The Entrepreneur
[unused] Is the New Madonna
[unused] Dear Joe ,
[unused] I know what you mean about being a journalist .
[unused] Almost every assignment is a challenge in a different way and it never seems to get easier .
[unused] I often feel as if I only get half the story sometimes , so I typically do a massive amount of reporting that is most often much more than I will ever need .
[unused] I think that is why I welcomed doing a book -- it gives one the ability to use so much of what is left on the cutting room floor of daily journalism .
[unused] Think of all the good stuff we all collect daily in our reporting that we never add to stories .
[unused] Most often reporters recount these tales with each other and with their sources rather than share them with the general public .
[unused] Much of it , of course , using the standards of top newspapers , cannot be used since it is largely gossip we are repeating , although it certainly could make for some very good stories .
[unused] I often wonder when a really great fictional book will be written about this era ( probably decades and decades hence as it is too close ) .
[unused] In any case , there certainly is no lack of information available about the moguls of technology now as they all become our current pop icons .
[unused] I would posit that Bill and Michael and Steve and Jerry have become the Madonnas of the current age of stock market mania and celebration of the entrepreneur .
[unused] So the shift in the image of Gates has been an interesting one for me to watch .
[unused] The smart- boy technologist is now being painted as the whiny bully .
[unused] I personally always thought it was a risk to pin the image of Microsoft on just one man-- at AOL , for example , there was a conscious effort to develop other " characters , " for lack of a better word .
[unused] So there , while you think of Case , you also think of Pittman and Leonsis and increasingly a range of other executives .
[unused] Steve Ballmer , of course , is now getting a lot more attention at Microsoft , but it still seems to be Bill 's show over there .
[unused] While I did not attend the trial -- I was lucky to be able to read your highly amusing and informative dispatches , several of which made me spit up my lunch laughing -- it certainly seemed as if the image of Bill Gates took a beating and the insular culture of Microsoft did not look so good .
[unused] That 's ironic , since I think it was just that insularity that helped them , much in the same way that AOL has benefited from being in the Virginia suburbs rather than in Silicon Valley .
[unused] AOL would never have existed if it had been founded here , I am sure , since its employees would have been mocked into obscurity by the digerati .
[unused] Out in the D.C. area , they looked positively exciting next to all the government -oriented contractors .
[unused] I wonder if that means geography is destiny , and it 's still location , location , location .
[unused] From where I am sitting , I think the Microsoft trial has been the really obvious turning point between the computer era and the digital age .
[unused] I think it almost does not matter what the judge does since it 's clear that the balance of power is shifting again , although it not clear where it will land .
[unused] Will the strongman of the era be AOL , AT&T , Microsoft , or one of the big media companies ?
[unused] Or will it be none of them because the Internet allows and encourages a plethora of strong companies and a complex interconnection of businesses where none are allowed to dominate ?
[unused] I always use two simple words when people tell me that one company -- whether it is AOL or Microsoft or Disney -- is in charge of all our destinies : Babylon was .
[unused] That incredible empire dominated the world and I imagine it did not seem possible to people living then that anyone could loosen that empire 's grip on humanity .
[unused] But we all know how that story turned out .
[unused] Now I am getting way too philosophical , but this is my final missive , so why not ?
[unused] Perhaps you could hasten a prediction of where this is all going .
[unused] As for me , I 'll stick with my philosophy of reporting and , I guess , life -- nobody knows .
[unused] Cheers , Kara
